<Layout title="Wave Riding Techniques - Surf Deeper" description="Master the art of riding waves with proper bottom turns, top turns, and cutbacks. Learn to read and ride different parts of the wave.">
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>Wave Riding Techniques</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">Master the art of riding waves</p>
  </header>

  <section class="technique-overview">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>Once you've caught a wave, the real fun begins. Wave riding is about reading the wave, positioning yourself correctly, and using the wave's energy to perform turns and maneuvers.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="wave-reading">
    <h2>Reading the Wave</h2>
    <div class="reading-grid">
      <div class="reading-card">
        <h3>Wave Anatomy</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Peak:</strong> The highest point where the wave breaks</li>
          <li><strong>Shoulder:</strong> The unbroken part of the wave</li>
          <li><strong>Pocket:</strong> The steep, powerful section</li>
          <li><strong>Lip:</strong> The top edge of the breaking wave</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="reading-card">
        <h3>Where to Position</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Stay in the pocket for speed and power</li>
          <li>Use the shoulder for turns and maneuvers</li>
          <li>Avoid the white water after the wave breaks</li>
          <li>Look ahead to plan your next move</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="basic-turns">
    <h2>Basic Turns</h2>
    <div class="turns-grid">
      <div class="turn-card">
        <h3>Bottom Turn</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Compress your legs as you go down the wave</li>
          <li>Look where you want to go</li>
          <li>Use your back foot to steer</li>
          <li>Keep your weight centered</li>
          <li>Generate speed for your next move</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="turn-card">
        <h3>Top Turn</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the wave's energy to go up</li>
          <li>Compress at the top of the wave</li>
          <li>Look down the line</li>
          <li>Use your front foot to steer</li>
          <li>Come back down with speed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="turn-card">
        <h3>Cutback</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Turn back toward the breaking part</li>
          <li>Use your back foot to pivot</li>
          <li>Look where you want to go</li>
          <li>Keep your weight centered</li>
          <li>Generate speed for the next section</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stance-and-balance">
    <h2>Stance and Balance</h2>
    <div class="stance-grid">
      <div class="stance-card">
        <h3>Basic Stance</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Feet shoulder-width apart</li>
          <li>Front foot at 45-degree angle</li>
          <li>Back foot perpendicular to stringer</li>
          <li>Bend your knees slightly</li>
          <li>Keep your weight centered</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="stance-card">
        <h3>Balance Tips</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Look where you want to go</li>
          <li>Use your arms for balance</li>
          <li>Stay relaxed and loose</li>
          <li>Bend your knees to absorb bumps</li>
          <li>Keep your core engaged</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="common-mistakes">
    <h2>Common Mistakes</h2>
    <div class="mistakes-grid">
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <h3>Looking Down</h3>
        <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Looking at your feet or the board</p>
        <p><strong>Fix:</strong> Always look where you want to go</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <h3>Stiff Stance</h3>
        <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Standing too straight and rigid</p>
        <p><strong>Fix:</strong> Bend your knees and stay loose</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <h3>Poor Weight Distribution</h3>
        <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Leaning too far forward or back</p>
        <p><strong>Fix:</strong> Keep your weight centered over your feet</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="practice-drills">
    <h2>Practice Drills</h2>
    <div class="drills-grid">
      <div class="drill-card">
        <h3>On Land</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Balance Board:</strong> Practice your stance</li>
          <li><strong>Yoga:</strong> Improve flexibility and balance</li>
          <li><strong>Skateboarding:</strong> Practice turning and balance</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="drill-card">
        <h3>In the Water</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Small Waves:</strong> Practice basic turns</li>
          <li><strong>White Water:</strong> Practice balance and stance</li>
          <li><strong>Repetition:</strong> Do the same turn over and over</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pro-tips">
    <h2>Pro Tips</h2>
    <ul class="tips-list">
      <li><strong>Read the Wave:</strong> Look ahead and plan your moves</li>
      <li><strong>Stay in the Pocket:</strong> That's where the power is</li>
      <li><strong>Use the Wave's Energy:</strong> Don't fight it, work with it</li>
      <li><strong>Practice One Thing:</strong> Master one turn before moving to the next</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <footer class="technique-footer">
    <p><em>Wave riding is about flow, not force</em></p>
  </footer>
</Layout>

